<body>

<h1>@HI{{rashii}}</h1>

<h2> Formation </h2>


<p>
<dl>
<dt>(A)
<ol>
<li>@N1{{}} <strong>@HI{{rashii}}</strong> @N2{{}}
</ol>
<dt>(B)
<ol>
<li>@Vplain{{}} <strong>@HI{{rashii}}</strong>
<li>@Ai{{}} <strong>@HI{{rashii}}</strong>
<li>@Ana{{}} <strong>@HI{{rashii}}</strong>
<li>@N{{}} <strong>@HI{{rashii}}</strong>
</ol>
</dl>
</p>

<h2> Definition </h2>

(A) means that @N2{{}} possesses the properties of an ideal form of @N1{{}}.
<p></p>

In usage (B) <strong>@HI{{rashii}}</strong> is an auxiliary adjective that indicates that the preceding sentence
is the speaker's conjecture based on what he has heard, seen or read. First-hand information is not invovled.
<p></p>

